                    <p>OpenStack: the open alternative to cloud lock-in
Invented by Rackspace and NASA.</p>
<p>
OpenStack® is an open and scalable operating system for building public and private clouds. It provides both large and small organizations an alternative to closed cloud environments, reducing the risks of lock-in associated with proprietary platforms. OpenStack offers flexibility and choice through a highly engaged community of over 6,000 individuals and over 190 companies including Rackspace®, Dell, HP, IBM, and Red Hat®.</p>
